{"metadata":{"title":"PIDFile","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","symbolKind":"enum"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"process ID of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"list","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"PID File Lifecycle","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" detects stale PID files by checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether the recorded process is still running.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"Thread Safety","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Thread-Safety"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"title":"Type Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/terminate(bundleURL:gracePeriod:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PID